metadata.name: The Storm ⛈ #22
metadata.description: Seemingly quiet amidst literary parlors and gilded seclusion, Emily Dickinson's life was likely at the mercy of a storm of emotions and feelings. In this work of generative art fully encoded in p5.js, the feelings of the people she lived with find an abstract representation, sometimes with fragments of her three her poems about storm.

metadata.name: We Are Alone Together #283
metadata.description:
We meander through the flows of life, alone but together. This experience — an ultimately solitary one — is communicated but never truly shared. Our consciousnesses live in a perpetual separated state, alone but together.

metadata.name: Solace #197
metadata.description:
Solace is an algorithm that generates artworks of sand dunes. It draws hundreds of thousands of tiny points according to a probability distribution calculated from the positions of the dunes.

The logic to divide the dunes into light and dark sides is simple, but produces some interesting chaotic behaviour. These are details that weren't hard-coded but emerge organically, such as the patterns on the spines of the dunes or the stripes around their bases.

Please note that the algorithm can take some time to run, especially when the number of dunes is high.

Created by lunarean.

metadata.name: Lepidoptera #60
metadata.description:
I love trying to capture the textures and colors found in nature and reproduce them with code. Lepidoptera is inspired by the species of the same name.

Features include: color palette, medium hatching count, large hatching count, noise offset, and noise level.

p5.js

metadata.name: Copenhagen Interpretation #52
metadata.description:
The Copenhagen Interpretation of quantum physics suggests that objects don't have physical properties until being observed.

In this generative piece by itsgalo and Spøgelsesmaskinen, a set of objects are being held in "superposition" and finally positioned when observed and minted.

Use mouse/touch to zoom, pan, and rotate. Press 's' to grab a screenshot. Best viewed in Firefox.

metadata.name: Impending Cloths #13
metadata.description:
IC makes use of fabric's potential for contrasts.
The same piece of cloth can seem to be falling, perfectly still and ready to be blown away, all at the same time.
It can look "very digital" while also achieving a high degree of texture. And so on, and so forth. Contrast and potential.
Also, "h" can be pressed to download in high resolution, although it may take up to a minute.

metadata.name: Tangled #24
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Divide By Circle Unsquared #3
metadata.description:
This special edition of Divide By Circle uses only 2 color designs which were not possible in the original. The aspect ratio has been "unsquared" to 3:2 for postcard and poster printing.

This set will be self minted and air dropped to collectors using a lottery system where iterations of Divide by Circles are the tickets. Winners will be chosen by generating a random number up to 512 and checking who owns that Divide by Circle. These are limited to one per person, so another number will be picked if there are any repeats. Once awarded the winner is free to sell or transfer the token.

A limited run of 25 postcards will be printed, signed, and numbered for each iteration in the set. The original 25 winners have a month to contact me via email or twitter with a postage address to send the card.

Due to the unpredictable nature of the postal system I can't guarantee everyone will receive their postcard but I will try my best. If there are any unclaimed cards after a month, they will be given away by other means. Thank you!

By Frank Force @KilledByAPixel
Made with JavaScript and Three.js
Click to randomize divisions and flip colors!

Live Mode Controls
1 - Save 2048x3072 png with SSAA
2 - Toggle noise
3 - Toggle animation
4 - Randomize every 10 seconds

metadata.name: Shift #135
metadata.description:
A generative algorithm honing the power of vertical displacement.

How simple may a generative algorithm be while simultaneously staying diverse enough for each art piece to be truly unique? Shift is the result of an exploration into this space, basing its existence on two principles — dissection and vertical shifting. Each variable in this art engine has been meticulously weighted, giving rise to high diversity and the possibility of epic combinations. 

Shift is a series of 888 unique pieces.

############

Display resolution is 1000x1400. Press ’s’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x8400 hi-res image. This may take a while to generate depending on your hardware.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022

metadata.name: The Emoji Finder Game 🔎 #61
metadata.description:
This is a 'Where's Waldo'-like video game(!) that procedurally generates one of seven fun and hectic "biomes" to search through. Find the specified emoji before time runs out to win! 

The seven biomes are: Safari, Ocean, Space, Kitchen, Twitter, Forest, and City. Share your game links with friends! 

Created by Michael Perusse | https://twitter.com/mrperusse
